Place two racks in the upper and lower thirds of the over and preheat to 350 F.

Beat 8 oz butter, 1 c brown sugar, and 1 c white sugar in a stand mixer with 
the paddle attachment. Mix in 2 eggs and 2 tsp vanilla. Add 3 c flour, 1 1/2 
tsp baking powder, 1 tsp baking soda, 1 1/2 tsp salt, and 8 oz chocolate chips, 
and mix just until combined.

Scoop balls of dough 1-2 tbsp in size onto a cookie sheet, and bake 12-15 
minutes, or until golden brown. 

Makes about 3 dozen cookies.


Ingredients: 
8 oz unsalted butter
1 c dark brown sugar
1 c white sugar
2 eggs
2 tsp vanilla extract
3 c whole-wheat flour
1 1/2 tsp baking powder
1 tsp baking soda
1 1/2 tsp salt
8 oz bittersweet chocolate chips
